<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC050F4644FB4176FB" box="[879,1185,368,389]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">NYCTIDROMUS DERBYANUS</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
GOULD, 1838
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF84FFBC054646A2FC7776D3" blockId="35.[806,1421,406,520]" box="[806,919,406,427]" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC054646A2FC7776D3" box="[806,919,406,427]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">Definition</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34B6535FF84FFBC05464680FB71730A" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF84FFBC05464680FC34757F" blockId="35.[806,1421,406,520]" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">
Previously 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC05CF4680FADF76B1" authorityName="Gould" authorityYear="1838" box="[943,1343,436,457]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="albicollis" subSpecies="derbyanus">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC05CF4680FADF76B1" box="[943,1343,436,457]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">Nyctidromus albicollis derbyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is elevated to full species status and is the sister species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC052546C6FC2D757F" baseAuthorityName="J. F. Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[837,973,498,519]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albicollis">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC052546C6FC2D757F" box="[837,973,498,519]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. albicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF84FFBC05464506FC76753F" blockId="35.[806,1422,562,706]" box="[806,918,562,583]" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC05464506FC76753F" box="[806,918,562,583]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF84FFBC05464564FBC875BA" blockId="35.[806,1422,562,706]" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">
Noticeably larger than both 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC02F84565FAC1751D" baseAuthorityName="J. F. Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[1176,1313,592,614]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albicollis">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC02F84565FAC1751D" box="[1176,1313,592,614]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. albicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC03124565FC9D75FC" baseAuthorityName="Sennett" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="merrilli">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC03124565FC9D75FC" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. merrilli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Back, crown, outer primaries and secondaries are distinctly reddish in colour. Not as dark in colour as 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC05F84599FBC175B9" baseAuthorityName="J. F. Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[920,1057,684,706]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albicollis">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC05F84599FBC175B9" box="[920,1057,684,706]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. albicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF84FFBC054645D9FC7D747A" blockId="35.[806,1421,749,1138]" box="[806,925,749,770]" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC054645D9FC7D747A" box="[806,925,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEE36BEFF84FFBC0546443FFB71730A" blockId="35.[806,1421,749,1138]" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">
Genetic evidence in this study is consistent with 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC0546441EFC4F7447" baseAuthorityName="J. F. Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[806,943,810,831]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albicollis">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC0546441EFC4F7447" box="[806,943,810,831]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. albicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being split into three phylogenetic species (
<figureCitation id="136A2A3BFF84FFBC05E8447CFC2B7426" box="[904,971,840,862]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="20.[164,243,1723,1742]" captionTargetBox="[251,773,201,1687]" captionTargetId="graphics-3@20.[242,901,164,1688]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 6. A phylogeny of the genera Lurocalis, Nyctidromus, and Nyctiprogne within the South American clade, based on a maximum-likelihood (ML) analysis of a concatenated 5298-bp molecular data set. ML bootstrap values higher than 60 and Bayesian posterior probability values higher than 0.95 are displayed on the nodes. Names on the tree represent current taxonomy; names on the right represent those resulting from this revision (see text)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5346442" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5346442/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Members of the nominate subspecies remain as 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC05DE445CFBA77404" baseAuthorityName="J. F. Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[958,1095,871,893]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albicollis">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC05DE445CFBA77404" box="[958,1095,871,893]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. albicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC02B9445CFA6D7404" box="[1241,1421,871,893]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">
N. a. 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC03774453FA6D7404" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[1303,1421,871,892]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="derbyanus">derbyanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is elevated to full phylospecies status under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC05134491FBEB74C1" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1838" box="[883,1035,932,954]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="derbyanus">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC05134491FBEB74C1" box="[883,1035,932,954]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. derbyanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Some individuals identified as 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC054644F7FC2B74A0" box="[806,971,963,984]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">
N. a. 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC050444F7FC2B74A0" baseAuthorityName="J. F. Gmelin" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[868,971,963,984]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albicollis">albicollis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
may also belong to this phylospecies, particularly south of the Amazon River (see details in Discussion). The remaining four subspecies, 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC0546432BFC2A734B" box="[806,970,1054,1076]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. a. insularis</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC0581432BFB7F734B" box="[993,1183,1054,1076]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. a. intercedens</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC02D6432BFAAA734B" box="[1206,1354,1054,1076]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">
N. a. 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC0293432AFAAA734B" baseAuthorityName="Sennett" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1267,1354,1054,1075]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="merrilli">merrilli</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, and 
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC0546430AFC16732B" box="[806,1014,1086,1107]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. a. yucatanensis</emphasis>
, can be united as a phylogenetic species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C514D3DFF84FFBC05E74368FBE07309" baseAuthorityName="Sennett" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[903,1024,1116,1137]" class="Aves" family="Caprimulgidae" genus="Nyctidromus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Caprimulgiformes" pageId="35" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="merrilli">
<emphasis id="B925EAACFF84FFBC05E74368FBE07309" box="[903,1024,1116,1137]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="541">N. merrilli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below).
</paragraph>
